public class ModelPanel
extends javax.swing.JPanel
implements java.awt.event.ActionListener

A user inputs the number of folds for cross validation, and selects a model and its parameters. Creates the selected model and start building and testing it.

Method Detail

actionPerformed

public void actionPerformed(java.awt.event.ActionEvent evt)
Actions which a user clicks an 'Option' button or selects a model in a Model check box. If 'Option' button clicked, the parameter frame corresponding a selected model will be created and the window will popped out. If one model selected, reset a current parameter frame as a null. If the selected model is K-Means, then show a dialog for reidentifying the types of each attributes.

Specified by:
